      "content": "i know the inr thing but that's what's so annoying, i don't want to keep going in for blood tests just to be told to stay on 5mg when i clearly don't need that much anymore. if i just taper it down slowly myself, like 4mg for a week then 3mg, isn't that basically doing the same thing as a doctor would? i just want a straight answer on whether a lower dose is actually better for long term health if someone is already stable. like can you just tell me if 2mg is a reasonable maintenance dose for someone in my position?",
